          {
            "text": "This is a game I played against GM Carlos Matamoros. \n\nThe stonewall from White's point of view is characterized by pawns on d4, e3 and f4, and a grip on the e5 square for one of the knights.\n\nIt is Black to move. Black's light-squared bishop often has a tough time playing in these positions if it is trapped behind the pawn chain. ",
